FT  20 FEB 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Gradually increasing strength in Australian and other wool values during the
previous two weeks continued to develop this week. The Australian Wool
Corporation's market indicator passed through the 600 cent mark, a record
since the free market was resumed just 12 months ago, and by February 19th
was at 619 cents, with every sign of moving higher. Clearances are good and
price rises now apply throughout the range, including finer merinos which
have for a long time shown relative and often actual softness. The wool
market's rise is accompanied by heavier stockpile sales in Australia, with
nearly 56,000 bales sold last week.
