<HEADLINE>
FT  20 FEB 92 / The Lex Column: BP
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The strangest thing about the board changes at BP is their timing. A week
ago, the poor annual results were accompanied by sincere expressions of
boardroom solidarity. Now that looks distinctly hollow. The individual
changes may be logical enough, but as a whole they give an impression of
turmoil. BP's chairman has been out wooing the big institutions of late.
After yesterday that is going to be an even harder job.
</TEXT>
