<TEXT>
Sir, While it is true, as reported by Clive Cookson ('BTG sell-off likely to
see only two bidders' February 19), that our joint venture with Sir Ronald
Mason has withdrawn from the bidding process for BTG, the inference drawn
that we are dissatisfied in any way with Price Waterhouse is incorrect.
In extremely difficult circumstances imposed by government on the
privatisation process, Sir Ronald Mason and I found the PW team to be
unfailingly helpful and highly professional. We would like to record our
thanks to them.
The tortuous and constrained process imposed by government has, no doubt,
been affected to some extent by the imminent general election.
However, the twin objectives of obtaining the highest price, while requiring
continued investment in new technologies, may be unattainable through a
venture capital route and privatisation.
