FT  20 FEB 92 / Arts: Death and the Maiden - Duke of York's Theatre
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MALCOLM RUTHERFORD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Death and the Maiden, widely acclaimed as the play of the year when it first
opened at the Theatre Upstairs, Royal Court last summer, has transferred to
the Duke of York's theatre for an unlimited run. Ariel Dorfman's piece is
about the transition from dictatorship to democracy in what looks like
Chile, but could be almost anywhere. With Juliet Stevenson and Michael
Byrne, above, and Bill Paterson.
</TEXT>
