FT  19 FEB 92 / UK News (Employment): Engineering pay levels fall
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MEDIAN pay settlement levels in engineering companies fell to 4.5 per cent
in the three months to January. They dropped from 4.9 per cent in the
quarter to December, according to the Engineering Employers' Federation.
The November-January figures, collated from 258 settlements, include 15
settlements where no increase is to be paid for the foreseeable future. The
federation has also reported 16 other short-term deferments which have not
been included.
The upper quartile of the November-January settlements was 5.1 per cent
against 5.5 per cent in October-December. However, the lower quartile
increased from 3.85 per cent to 4 per cent.
