FT  19 FEB 92 / Polystyrene recycling plant
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LINPAC Plastics International, the food packaging group, has opened the
first polystyrene recycling plant in Europe with a capacity to process 2,500
tonnes of waste.
The 21,000 sq ft plant based near Macclesfield, Cheshire, will collect
polystyrene packaging waste such as vending cups from fast-food restaurants
and local authorities and use it for multi-layer polystyrene-foam egg
cartons.
